choose to get a belt waist slimmer is to help them sweat more. When you wear it, your body temperature during exercises gets even higher, and the corset helps you maintain that high temperature throughout the entire duration of the workout, thereby helping you to sweat more.</p><p>Now, how will it  help you to lose weight? Well, when your overall body temperature is higher, it enables you to sweat more and get rid of excess water  meaning that a 30-minute workout can become much more effective with a belt. It also helps you look less puffy, as extra water can make us look very bloated.&nbsp;</p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670784163075" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1670784163075"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000">Supports Your Back&nbsp;</font></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670784163062" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1670784163062" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">Along with this, </span><a href="https://www.umms.org/ummc/health-services/orthopedics/services/spine/patient-guides/lumbar-compression-fractures" class="" target="_blank" style="font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">compression is considered as one of the most vital factors in recovery of back injuries</a><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">, which is another reason why many physios recommend their patients to get one. The cool thing is that you can wear the waist trimmer even when you’re not exercising - for example, when you’re doing housework or even in the office.</span><br></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1700474502476" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1700474502476" data-row-gap="0px" data-extraclass=""><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1686320640542" data-id="1686320640542"><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1700474502378" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1700474502378" data-layout-lg="6+6" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="6+6" data-layout-sm="6+6" data-layout-xs="8+4" data-row-gap="0px"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-8" id="c-1686566620521" data-id="1686566620521"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1700474502456" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1700474502456"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><b>Tips From the Champ</b></h2></div></div></div><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-4" id="c-1686566621695" data-id="1686566621695"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1700474502389" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1700474502389" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-right-lg gf-elm-right-md gf-elm-right-sm gf-elm-right-xs" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/d583efb1-a2f6-4d53-8a26-d6ddafaa60fd/7350738.png" alt="" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="512" height="512" data-width="50%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="512" natural-height="512"></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1700474502371" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1700474502371"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="">It’s likely that when you hear the phrase “slimming belt,” you don't think about any back problems. However, physiotherapists and chiropractors often advise patients with spinal and back injuries to use waist trimmers and compression bandages. This is mainly due to the fact that these items can help support the back by straightening it and maintaining the correct posture of the patient.&nbsp;</div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1700474502357" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1700474502357" data-layout-lg="6+6" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="6+6" data-layout-sm="6+6" data-layout-xs="12+12" data-row-gap="0px"><div class="gf_column gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1686564763470" data-id="1686564763470"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1700474502470" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1700474502470" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-exc=""><a href="https://torokhtiy.com/pages/oleksiy-torokhtiy" target="_blank"><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/fc0a1a19-2e31-4fa8-a43b-9c408a123923/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/Oleksiy.jpg" alt="" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="531" height="533" data-width="20%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="531" natural-height="533"></a></div></div></div><div class="gf_column gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1686564765807" data-id="1686564765807"><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1700474502463" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1700474502463"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><b><a href="https://torokhtiy.com/pages/oleksiy-torokhtiy" class="" target="_blank">Oleksiy Torokhtiy</a></b></p></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1700474502356" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1700474502356"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><span style="font-weight: 700;">Olympic Weightlifting&nbsp;</span><span style="font-weight: 700; color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">Champion</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670784163068" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1670784163068"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">When Do You Need a Waist Trimmer Belt?</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670784163074" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1670784163074" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Typically, the best time to wear a waist trimmer belt is during cardio and some weightlifting workouts. This is because their main function is to help raise your body temperature and keep it high during the entire workout, thus helping you burn more calories in less time. Having said that, it’s best to choose a waist-slimming belt when doing <a href="https://www.gaiam.com/blogs/discover/what-is-steady-state-cardio" class="" target="_blank">steady-state cardio</a> and for a longer period of time. During HIIT classes or fitness, wearing a trimmer belt can make the entire workout more uncomfortable, and also not as effective because, typically, these  training sessions are associated with elevated heart rates throughout their duration.&nbsp;</p><p>However, some people prefer to wear a waist-slimming belt, even during regular gym workouts. They feel it helps keep their lower back warm while still providing some support and keeping their posture correct.</p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1671101552931" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1671101552931" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/48193d66-e428-4f05-8de4-2ad4d17d3982/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/training-waist-belt-torokhtiy.jpg" alt="Waist Trimmer Belt" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670784163150" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1670784163150"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">What to Look For in Waist Trimmer Belts?</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670784163064" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1670784163064" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>So far, we’ve discussed the best waist trimmers on the market, what the benefits of wearing them and when you need to use them. Now, it’s time to talk about what you need to look for in a waist-slimming belt before you decide which one to buy. Below, we will talk about the most important factors to consider when picking a waist trimmer for you.&nbsp;</p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670784163113" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1670784163113"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000">1. Design</font></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670784163041" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1670784163041" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>When it comes to design, you want to look for a belt that covers your entire waist and your lower back. That way, not only to help you sweat more, but it will also feel more supportive. Additionally, it’s vital to look for a belt that can be tightly sealed - you don’t want it to fit loosely, as it won’t help you burn more calories, and it will feel super uncomfortable when you’re working out. Finally, when it comes to structure, it’s vital to consider flexibility - a good waist slimming belt should be flexible and able to adjust to your body shape.&nbsp;</p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670784163000" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1670784163000"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000"><strong>2. Resistance</strong></font></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670784163043" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1670784163043" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Another vital factor is the good fit. The whole idea behind the waist-trimming belt is to create compression around your waist and lower back, so you need to find a belt that fits just tight enough. Anything that’s too loose is simply not worth getting it. Here, the most vital part is to look for a belt made out of high-quality materials and to make sure you have the right size. Most waist slimmers on the market come in various sizes, and they’re also adjustable, but if it’s too big from the get-go, adjusting it won’t help you much.</p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670784163135" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1670784163135"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000">3. Durability</font></h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670784163082" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1670784163082" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>When you decide to spend your earned money on a fitness accessory, be sure it can lasts more than a few training sessions. When it comes to waist slimming belts, it is important to look for those that are made from high quality materials - 100% latex-free neoprene is a must-have. You have to make sure the material is not slippery and that it doesn’t absorb your sweat, otherwise, you will have to change it pretty quickly due to the bad odor that will start to appear.&nbsp;</p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670784163099" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1670784163099"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000">4. Price/Quality</font></h3></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1670784163004" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1670784163004" data-row-gap="0px" data-extraclass="" data-layout-lg="12" data-layout-md="12" data-layout-sm="12" data-layout-xs="12" style="display: block;"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1658828961229" data-id="1658828961229"><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670784163115" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1670784163115" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Many people assume that more expensive equals better quality. But, in fact, that’s often not the case. When it comes to fitness accessories, in a lot of cases, you pay more money for the brand than for the product. Our advice would be to not to fall for marketing and instead go for a high-quality belt, even if it doesn’t have a well-known brand name.</p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670784163160" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1670784163160" data-resolution="3000x3000" style="display: block;"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/c7a08f31-2d54-49c5-9e1d-db7cf73e6d20/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/training-waist-belt-showing-torokhtiy.jpg" alt="best sweat belt" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670784163047" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1670784163047"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">How to Use a Waist Trimmer Belt?</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670784163088" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1670784163088" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Luckily for us all, wearing and using a waist trimmer belt is not rocket science. In fact, it takes just a few steps to put it on and take it off. Let’s take a look at them.&nbsp;</p><p><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;"><strong>Step 1:</strong> On the bare skin of your stomach, take the belt and place it with the closing mechanism facing forward.</span><br></p><p><strong>Step 2: </strong>After that, grab both ends and wrap around until you feel the fit is tight enough. (You should be able to properly breathe in and out while wearing it, so try doing this in order to find the right fit).</p><p><strong>Step 3:</strong> Once you’re sure you’ve found the right compression, lock in the belt using its mechanism (usually a lock and hook).&nbsp;</p><p><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">From now on, you can start doing your workout. At the end of it, when you take the belt off, you can either wipe the sweat off or just wash it if you don't intend to use it anytime soon.&nbsp;</span></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670784163063" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1670784163063"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">FAQ</h2></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670784163092" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1670784163092"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Do Waist Trimmer Belts Work?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670784163013" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1670784163013"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Waist trimmer belts won’t magically melt off your fat. They’re not magical devices and if someone tells you that, then they’re lying. However, waist trimmer belts do help you burn sweat more, get rid of excess water while you are working out and, along with a balanced diet, can help you reduce body and waist fat and achieve your desired physique.</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670784163072" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1670784163072"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Why Do Fitness Wear Vests?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670784163133" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1670784163133" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><a href="https://www.health.harvard.edu/blog/the-skinny-on-freezing-fat-2020031218990" class="" target="_blank">Wearing a waist-slimming belt on its own won’t help you lose fat</a>. However, if you combine wearing a belt with a calorie deficit and a few cardio training sessions per week, you will definitely see your belly fat melt away.&nbsp;</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670784163109" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1670784163109"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Can I Wear a Tummy Belt While Sleeping?</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1670784163054" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1670784163054" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">It’s generally not recommended to wear a belt around your waist while sleeping.This is because wearing it at night can have a negative impact on proper digestion and lead to acid reflux. This will most likely make you feel uncomfortable and thus impact the quality of your sleep.</p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p><p style="font-size: 20px; font-family: Montserrat, HelveticaNeue, &quot;Helvetica Neue&quot;, sans-serif; text-align: inherit!important; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"></p></div></div><div data-label="Liquid" data-key="liquid" data-atomgroup="module" id="m-1671370715426" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-liquid" 